article.headline: Northeastern 79, VA Commonwealth 74
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Shawn James scored a career-high 26 points and added 10 rebounds and 10 blocked shots as Northeastern held off Virginia Commonwealth 79-74 on Saturday. Northeastern (13-8, 9-4 Colonial) led by as many as 13 in the second half, but VCU pulled within five, 76-71, on Alexander Harper's 3-pointer with 27.9 seconds left. But Jose Juan Barea hit a free throw and Bobby Kelly scored on a layup to put the game out of reach. B.A. Walker hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer to account for the final score. James was 10-of-13 from the floor and his effort was the third triple-double of his career. Barea had 22 points and nine assists. The Rams (15-6, 9-4) were by Nick George with 28 points and 13 rebounds, and Walker with 15 points. VCU led early, but Kelly tied the score at 13-13 with a jumper with 14:44 left in the first half. Barea hit a 3-pointer with 14:22 left to give Northeastern the lead for good. Barea also hit a driving layup in the final seconds of the half to give Northeastern a 37-30 halftime lead.
